headline: Got $200? 2 Healthcare Stocks to Buy and Hold Forever
summary: Healthcare is considered a defensive industry, since good medical care is needed regardless of economic or market conditions.  Here are two great examples: Bristol Myers Squibb (NYSE: BMY) and DexCom (NASDAQ: DXCM).  Developing novel medicines is risky and time-consuming, and comes with a maze of regulatory challenges.
